FBIS3-57855 "drweu002_o_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 CYPRUS Kliridhis Hails Joint Defense Doctrine `Significance' NC3112122993 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1000 GMT 31 Dec 93 NC3112122993 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis has hailed the new Greek-Cypriot defense doctrine's significance, stressing that peace in Cyprus will be more secure as Greece becomes more involved. The president said the situation would change significantly when the invader knows that every new aggressive action in Cyprus implies a Greek-Turkish war. Kliridhis said the defense doctrine will be go into effect during the visit by Greek Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis and a delegation of senior military officials in early January. The president said this to National Guardsmen this morning when he visited National Guard posts in Nicosia. Defense Minister Kostandinos Iliadhis and National Guard Chief General Yeoryios Siradhakis accompanied Kliridhis.
